hopobject.body: One moment, please order vydexafil There's an awful lot going on under the hood of Bay Trail — see our slidedeck gallery above — but perhaps the most interesting part might have less to do with the CPU or GPU, and more the way they work in tandem with other components of the tablet silicon. Bay Trail dynamically allocates power between all four CPU cores, the graphics cores, a dedicated image signal processor for dual cameras, and even to connected displays. That means your tablet might not be as fast when you've got an external display connected, but on the flip side it means that when you need that processing power it'll be diverted wherever it's needed.
